<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Edit: Please read our sig/personal pic rules. Both mustn't be more than 15kbyte combined. - ShadowCross</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/ushadowcross.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shadowcross</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_purplespot.gif" BORDER=0> at: 6/24/02 7:11:45 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/umajestykvz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MajestykVZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/21/02 7:32:27 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Well, as I said-</span><hr size=1> Swipey, your bitterness makes you blind.<br>
<br>
No one here said EQ PvP is not broken.  My point is merely illustrating that a desire to engage in PvP is not in itself a manifestation of deeply rooted psychological problems, as is suggested by some of the posters here.<br>
<br>
As for your rule one referral to Kagero's comment:  If the 8 year old walks off the field then turns around and flips off the 350 pounder,  the 350 pounder has a moral obligation to smack the 8 year old up-side the head.<br>
<br>
PvP.  If, the game don't have it, it ain't worth playin'. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/uswipey.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Swipey</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/22/02 1:58:00 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Well, as I said-</span><hr size=1> I never said the desire to engage in PvP required someone to have deep rooted psychological probems.  <br>
<br>
I am, however, of the opinion that the particular ways in which EQ PvP is broken tends to draw a greater number of &quot;buttheads&quot; to the PvP servers.  Or maybe its the same number of buttheads per capita, but they're able to express their buttheadedness so much more clearly that it just seems like theres more of them.<br>
<br>
As for the 350 pounder's moral obligations vis-a-vis the peewee player : He should be picking on people his own size, and shouldn't ahve hit the peewee player in the first place, thus encouraging the little one to flip him off.  This holds especially true if the 350 pounder is claiming he plays EQFootball for the challenge.<br>
<br>
In straight EQ terms : Do you think its cool for high level players to camp the newbie zones and continually kill people who have zero chance against them, or do you think that is griefing? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/umoffonfurryhealer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Moffon Furryhealer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/22/02 2:06:54 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Well, as I said-</span><hr size=1> Don't assume things about anyone on any server and you'll be ok.  Stereotypes never work.<br>
<br>
I play on Rallos.  There's a lot of @#%$, and there's just as many people who go out of their way to help you.  There's @#%$ on other servers too.  The only difference is that we can fight the @#%$ until they leave the server in frustration.  It's actually a lot nicer place than you'd imagine.  I wouldn't have said the same thing a few months ago, but we worked hard for the peace we are enjoying.  Me, I'm bored though :/<br>
<br>
p.s. I speak of the high end game, theres still a lot of prick pk's sub 56.<br>
<br>
Moffon <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/ufricka.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fricka</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/22/02 2:12:49 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/~fricka/sig/5fricka60x56.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Well, as I said-</span><hr size=1> ::raises her hand::<br>
<br>
Please, can I be one of the folks who likes &quot;personal conflict&quot;? ;P Yes, I understand it was a &quot;general comment&quot; <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Personally, I like something called team competition. That way you have the cooperative elements of the &quot;bluebie&quot; game and yet  with the added element of competition with new opportunities for roleplaying as well.<br>
<br>
The Best of the Best competitions mimic the team competition feel as well.<br>
<br>
As for the questions about griefing on the broken PvP servers. I happily left all such questions behind when I left the servers and prefer not to be &quot;dragged back in&quot; as Pacino would say. <p><img src="http://www.thesafehouse.org/%7Efricka/sig/DAOCsig.jpg"><br><b>~Fricka</b>
