</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/upickkpockket999.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Pickk Pockket999</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/23/02 3:43:37 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Well, as I said-</span><hr size=1> I love Sullon Zek but I have to admit that the server seems to have more than its fair share of immature idiots. Join the trade channel sometime for a prime example. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/usaereajaciabre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saere Ajaciabre</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_yellowspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/24/02 2:15:32 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Well, as I said-</span><hr size=1> Oh my Lord... I play on Innoruuk and on Vallon.  As for pvp, I prefer Vallon.  However, I decided to try Sullon about a week or so ago.  Flowers of Happiness was spamming the trade channel with &quot;GO GO GOOD TEAM&quot; and &quot;I AM A HAMSTER.&quot;<br>
<br>
That was the last of my adventure on SZ, and I went right back to Vallon.<br>
<br>
Edit -- I forgot to stay within topic and say what I had been thinking regarding players on pvp servers.  I agree that pvp is for those who enjoy dishing it out, and that's usually the side of pvp'ers get the most crap for.  On the other hand, you have to know how to take it as well.  My first time on pvp, I got killed by a couple of jerks who had been going around killing all the noobs in Blackburrow, picking them off one by one.  I took it personally, and was really upset.  That was quite a while ago.  This weekend I was playing one of my little noobs in Qeynos Hills, when two shorty casters came in doing the same thing.  They killed me, and as I was running back to get my corpse, I started laughing at all the other noobie corpses in the zone.  <br>
<br>
The point is, being a pvp'er isn't just about being someone who can dish out a bunch of crap.  It's someone who knows how to take it, and that to me says a lot about how mature a person can actually be. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/usaereajaciabre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saere Ajaciabre</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_yellowspot.gif" BORDER=0> at: 6/24/02 2:22:43 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/ustytchyapgud.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stytch Yapgud</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/24/02 4:14:23 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Well, as I said-</span><hr size=1> I like competing against other players sometimes.<br>
<br>
And when Im not in the mood to fight others then it still adds difficulty to trying to level that makes the game just that bit harder.<br>
<br>
I had many preconceptions about pvp till I tried it seriously.<br>
Remember our arguement many months ago majestyk?<br>
I guess I owe you not so much an apology but certainly an admittance that I wasnt as right as I thought.<br>
